**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Headers can be trivially spoofed by any attacker
- No cryptographic verification of service identity
- Trust boundary between internal/external is enforced only by network assumptions
- Lateral movement from one compromised service gives access to all
- No audit trail of which service made which request

**SECURE VERSION**:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');
const crypto = require('crypto');

